-- U.S. Public Ridership Fell in the First Quarter
-- B y   A i n h o a   G o y e n e c h e
-- 2013-06-14T13:27:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-14/u-s-public-ridership-fell-in-the-first-quarter-table-.html
Trips on public transportation  
in the U.S. fell in the first quarter from the same period
last year, according to the American Public Transportation
Association.     Americans taking public transportation fell to 2.59 billion
trips from the same quarter last year. Travel on light rail 
rose to 121.9 million in the first quarter.  SOURCE: American Public Transportation Association 